  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen using `HDWalletProvider` so we can use our own mnemonic / private keys, unit tests cannot run.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nIn our truffle configuration:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nrequire('dotenv').config();\r\nconst keys = require('./keys');\r\nconst HDWalletProvider = require('truffle-hdwallet-provider');\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen we declare our networks like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    development: {\r\n      provider: () => {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(keys, 'http://localhost:7545', 0, 10, false /* tried both true and false */);\r\n      },\r\n      // host: 'localhost',\r\n      // port: '7545',\r\n      network_id: '5777',\r\n    },\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen migrations work, but unit tests just fail with errors:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: the tx doesn't have the correct nonce. account has nonce of: 37 tx has nonce of: 36\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat's really odd is that we're able to run migrations, and from a truffle console issue operations too (Eg instanciate contracts etc).\r\nAnother interesting thing, if simply using mnemonic instead of private keys, the exact same things happens.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n```\r\nTruffle v5.0.22 (core: 5.0.22)\r\nSolidity - 0.5.9 (solc-js)\r\nNode v10.15.3\r\nWeb3.js v1.0.0-beta.37\r\n```",
